{
  "stem": "1581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the medical school of the University of Vienna.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, the medical school of Vienna was by far the leading medical authority in the world.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Names that are now saints in the medical science were my teachers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whether it was Sigmund Freud, or whether it was Wenckebach, or Eiselsberg, or Denk, or Kwastek.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All these names are in all medical books, mentioned all the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at the time, of course, I didn't know how lucky I was, but they were all my teachers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no Jewish faculty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I think-- I think Sigmund Freud was the only Jew that ever got a-- a professorship.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Once you were a Jew, you couldn't get further than to be a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That means you had lectures, and you were teaching.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you did not get any professorship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in constant fights with the radical right, with the student organizations they had at that time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The scars on the cheeks from the fencing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were dueling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had certain caps, like that showed them to be members of certain student organizations.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were absolute rabid anti-Semites.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it came to physical fights.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, whenever they approached us, usually five against one, using [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] funny names and assaulting us, we got into a fight.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were, at that time-- just as an aside-- we were studying anatomy, and we were dissecting bodies at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one of these fights, I vividly remember, wound up that we used corpses as weapons.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We just used bones or-- or arms, extremities.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As sad, as horrible as it sounds, it was very funny.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Interestingly enough, our anatomy professor was a former Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, he couldn't remain a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Otherwise, he wouldn't be a professor.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
